### 🎯 Exercise 01: Subnet for 8 offices using the network address fd00:1::/64

<br>

### CAI Method

![BitLength](img/BitLength.png)


&nbsp;
---
&nbsp;


__CONVERT *(Bit Value. NOT Length)*__  
  8 = 3 bits  


<br>


__ADD__  
  /64 + 3 bits = /67 (5th Hextet, 1st Hexadecimal, 2i)
  
  
<br>


__INSERT(*IPASOK Many Times*)__  

Expand the given IPv6 address:

`fd00:0001:0000:0000  :0000:  0000:0000:0000 /67`


<br>


1. Office: :0000:
2. Office: :2000:
3. Office: :4000:
4. Office: :6000:
5. Office: :8000:
6. Office: :A000:
7. Office: :C000:
8. Office: :E000:


