### DHCPv6

### 🎯 Exercise 09: Subnet for TELSTRA.COM for 107 offices using the network address fd00:6::/105  Use the 5th subnet for DHCP.

__CONVERT__  
  107 = 7 bits  


<br>


__ADD__  
  /105 + 7 bits = /112 (7th Hextet, 4th Hexadecimal, 1i)
  
  
<br>


__INSERT(*IPASOK Many Times*)__  

Expand the given IPv6 address:

`fd00:0006:0000:0000:0000:0000 :0000: 0000 /112`


<br>


1. Office: :0000:
2. Office: :0001:
3. Office: :0002:
4. Office: :0003:
5. Office: :0004:


<br>

|             | IP Address                                   |
| ---         | ---                                          | 
| Network ANY | fd00:0006:0000:0000:0000:0000:0004:0000 /112 |
| 1st IP      | fd00:0006:0000:0000:0000:0000:0004:0001 /112 |
| Last IP     | fd00:0006:0000:0000:0000:0000:0004:FF7F /112 |
|             |                                              |
| 1st ANY     | fd00:0006:0000:0000:0000:0000:0004:FF80 /112 |
| Last ANY    | fd00:0006:0000:0000:0000:0000:0004:FFFF /112 |
|             |                                              |
| Not Net     | fd00:0006:0000:0000:0000:0000:0005:0000 /112 |


<br>
<br>


~~~
!@D1
conf t
 ipv6 unicast-routing
 !
 ipv6 dhcp pool TELSTRA.COM
  address prefix fd00:6::4:0/112
  domain-name TELSTRA.COM
  exit
 !
 vlan 30
  name TELSTRA.COM
  exit
 int vlan 30
  no shut
  ipv6 add fd00:6::4:1/112
  ipv6 dhcp server TELSTRA.COM
  ipv6 nd managed-config-flag
  ipv6 nd other-config-flag
  end
~~~

